## 2. Motion Rules (Premium Motion, Not Flashy)

### 2.1 Micro-animations Only

**Rule**: Duration 150-220ms. Easing: standard ease-out. Use motion to clarify state changes, not decorate.

**Animation Constants**:
```typescript
// src/shared/constants/animations.ts
export const ANIMATION = {
  duration: {
    micro: 150,   // Micro-interactions
    fast: 200,    // Standard transitions
    normal: 220,  // Max for micro-animations
  },
  easing: {
    easeOut: Easing.out(Easing.ease),
  },
} as const;
```

**Usage**:
```typescript
Animated.timing(value, {
  toValue: 1,
  duration: ANIMATION.duration.fast,
  easing: ANIMATION.easing.easeOut,
  useNativeDriver: true,
}).start();
```

---

### 2.2 Disable "Bouncy" Transitions by Default

**Rule**: Avoid spring overshoot for core navigation/controls. Springs are fine for tiny affordances (e.g., toggles) if subtle.

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
// Standard ease-out for navigation
Animated.timing(translateX, {
  toValue: 0,
  duration: 200,
  easing: Easing.out(Easing.ease),
}).start();
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Bouncy spring for navigation (too playful)
Animated.spring(translateX, {
  toValue: 0,
  overshootClamping: false, // Creates bounce
}).start();
```

**Exception**: Subtle springs for toggle switches, checkboxes (tiny affordances only).

---

### 2.3 Skeleton Loading Over Spinners

**Rule**: Spinners feel cheap when overused. Use skeletons for list and card loading. Use spinners only for short actions (<1s perceived).

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
// Skeleton for list loading
{isLoading ? (
  <SkeletonList count={5} />
) : (
  <FlatList data={items} />
)}

// Spinner only for short actions
<Button
  loading={isSubmitting}
  onPress={handleSubmit}
/>
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Spinner for list loading (feels cheap)
{isLoading ? (
  <ActivityIndicator size="large" />
) : (
  <FlatList data={items} />
)}
```

