## 3. Content Rules (The Hidden Luxury Lever)

### 3.1 Reduce Visible UI "Noise"

**Rule**: Fewer labels. Shorter copy. More whitespace. Fewer simultaneous call-to-actions.

**✅ GOOD**:
```typescript
// Clean, minimal
<View>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.h1}>Balance</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.currency}>$12,345.67</Text>
</View>
```

**❌ BAD**:
```typescript
// Too much noise
<View>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.label}>Current Account Balance</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.body}>Your balance as of today</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.currency}>$12,345.67</Text>
  <Text style={TEXT_STYLES.caption}>Last updated: 2 minutes ago</Text>
  <Button title="View Details" />
  <Button title="Add Transaction" />
  <Button title="Export" />
</View>
```

---

### 3.2 Numbers Should Feel "Instrument-Grade"

**Rule**: For finance/data screens, align decimals, use tabular numerals if available, keep formatting consistent.

**Implementation**:
```typescript
// Tabular numerals (monospaced numbers)
const currencyStyle = {
  ...TEXT_STYLES.currency,
  fontVariant: ['tabular-nums'], // Aligns decimals
};

// Consistent formatting
const formatCurrency = (amount: number) => {
  return new Intl.NumberFormat('en-US', {
    style: 'currency',
    currency: 'USD',
    minimumFractionDigits: 2,
    maximumFractionDigits: 2,
  }).format(amount);
};
```

